{"blocks":[{"key":"7m76p","text":"This protocol describes a rapid method for detecting HiBiT-tagged proteins in zebrafish embryos following mRNA microinjection.

It is designed for efficiency, reproducibility, and compatibility with standard zebrafish workflows.

Key guidelines:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d5cnb","text":"Perform all steps using RNase-free reagents and consumables to prevent RNA degradation.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":24,"length":35}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bv35g","text":"Maintain embryos in E3 medium without additives (no methylene blue or HEPES) prior to lysis.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":20,"length":27}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"evdsb","text":"Use consistent embryo numbers (20–30 per sample) to allow accurate comparison of luminescence values.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":4,"length":44}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dsbef","text":"For detection, use Promega Nano-Glo HiBiT Lytic Reagent or a comparable luciferase-compatible lysis buffer.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":19,"length":36}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8od37","text":"Keep samples on ice whenever possible and minimize unnecessary freeze–thaw cycles after lysis.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
